# Kernel config fragment merged onto the riscv defconfig (linux/CMakeLists.txt).
#
# The console lives on the design's AXI UART Lite. The command line comes from the
# device tree's /chosen node, which the SoC generator emits (console selection and
# earlycon describe the design's UART) - no CONFIG_CMDLINE is baked in, so one kernel
# image serves any hardware generation. HZ is pinned so the timeconst generation is
# deterministic across hosts. The rootfs is an initramfs embedded into the Image -
# the SD controller has no mainline driver, so there is no storage for Linux to mount.
# The initramfs description is a FIXED path in the kernel build dir; each boot image
# copies its own description there, so switching programs never reconfigures.
# AppArmor is useless on this SoC and its capability_names.h generation needs GNU
# sed (\L), which BSD/macOS sed lacks - the only known GNU-sed site in the build.
# CONFIG_SECURITY_APPARMOR is not set
CONFIG_SERIAL_UARTLITE=y
CONFIG_SERIAL_UARTLITE_CONSOLE=y
CONFIG_HZ_250=y
CONFIG_BLK_DEV_INITRD=y
CONFIG_INITRAMFS_SOURCE="@KBUILD_DESC@"
